text: The North Albany Clubhouse stands by itself in rural Albany County, Wyoming. It was built in 1928 as a community meeting center by local residents. It continues to serve as a community social center. The clubhouse was placed on the National Register of Historic Places on July 23, 1998. ==References== ==External links== * North Albany Clubhouse at the Wyoming State Historic Preservation Office Category:National Register of Historic Places in Albany County, Wyoming Category:Buildings and structures completed in 1928
title: North Albany Clubhouse
